            <h2>Fever</h2>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> Fever is a temporary rise in body temperature, often due to infection.</p>
            <p><strong>Causes:</strong> Viral/bacterial infections, heat exhaustion.</p>
            <p><strong>Symptoms:</strong> High temperature, chills, sweating.</p>
            <p><strong>Prevention:</strong> Stay hydrated, practice hygiene.</p>
            <p><strong>Treatment:</strong> Rest, hydration, fever reducers.</p>
        </div>        
        <div class="disease-card">
            <img src="/img/en/3_2.webp" alt="Influenza">
            <h2>Influenza</h2>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> A highly contagious respiratory infection.</p>
            <p><strong>Causes:</strong> Influenza virus spread via droplets.</p>
            <p><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Fever, body aches, fatigue.</p>
            <p><strong>Prevention:</strong> Flu vaccine, hand hygiene.</p>
            <p><strong>Treatment:</strong> Antivirals, rest, hydration.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="disease-card">
            <img src="/img/en/3_3.jpg" alt="Hypertension">
            <h2>Hypertension</h2>
            <p><strong>Description:</strong> High blood pressure increasing heart risks.</p>
            <p><strong>Causes:</strong> Obesity, stress, high salt intake.</p>
            <p><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Often silent; headaches, dizziness.</p>
            <p><strong>Prevention:</strong> Exercise, reduce salt, manage stress.</p>
            <p><strong>Treatment:</strong> BP medications, diet changes.</p>
        </div>
